gomodel:SYNGO_4822  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099060 replaced by GO:0099634" , "Rationale: Figure 3i: Immunofluorescence imaging showed co-localization of KCC2 (SLC12A5) and gephyrin (marker for inhibitory postsynapses).\n\nFigure 3j,k: \"Electron microscopy on WT adult spinal cord confirms accumulation of KCC2 along the plasma membrane of dendrites but not in axons. The ultrastructure of a spinal cord dendrite revealed that immunogold-labeled KCC2 (asterisks) is located in proximity to synapses.\"\n\nauthors conclude \"Thus, KCC2 is predominantly, but not exclusively, localized at gephyrin-positive inhibitory synapses ... KCC2 was expressed at synapses (Figure 3K). It was enriched at the periphery of the postsynaptic specialization, whereas gephyrin is known to form a postsynaptic matrix that coextends with the active zone.\"\n\nBased on the known transmembrane topology of this protein, \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was selected.. Experimental description: All experiments were performed in mice. e.g. from abstract: \"We show that KCC2 knockout mice died immediately after birth due to severe motor deficits that also abolished respiration.\"\n\nantibody:\n\"The KCC2 antiserum was raised in rabbits against the amino-terminal epitope CEDGDGGANPGDGNP coupled to BSA through the C-terminal cysteine and affinity purified\". This was also used for EM; \"Sections were incubated with KCC2 antiserum in 0.1% gelatine and 0.5% BSA in PBS and subsequently with goat anti-rabbit nano gold (Biotrend).\"\n\nprotein BLAST of this peptide against mouse proteome confirmed this is protein NP_065066 and gene Slc12a5" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4822" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

